ğŸ” What are Generator Functions?
Generator functions are special functions that can pause their execution and resume later, allowing us to work with iterators in a more flexible way. They are defined using the function* syntax and use the yield keyword to pause execution.

ğŸŒŸ Why Use Generator Functions?
1ï¸âƒ£ Stateful Iteration: They maintain their state between executions, making it easier to work with complex sequences.
2ï¸âƒ£ Simplified Asynchronous Code: Generators can be combined with promises to handle asynchronous operations in a more readable manner.

